at the famous
training base in North Carolina.

02:41.428 --> 02:44.998 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Testing found contamination from
fuel tanks
and a dry cleaner.

02:45.098 --> 02:49.302 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hundreds of thousands of people
passed through
that base, and some developed
diseases like

02:49.403 --> 02:52.472 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
leukemia, liver cancer, and
Parkinson's disease.

02:52.572 --> 02:55.976 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Department of Veterans
Affairs says it
will pay up to $2.2 billion.

02:56.076 --> 03:01.248 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The Japanese
company Takata
will plead guilty in a federal
investigation

03:01.348 --> 03:07.087 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
